        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 25 at 5:46PM MDT by NWS Missoula MT</headline>
        <description>At 545 PM MDT/445 PM PDT/, Doppler radar was tracking a strong
thunderstorm 13 miles west of Conner, or 27 miles southwest of
Hamilton, moving northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Hamilton, Darby, Conner, Charlos Heights, and Como.

This includes Highway 93 S between mile markers 22 and 43.
</description>
        <instruction>This storm may intensify, so be certain to monitor local radio
stations and available television stations for additional information
and possible warnings from the National Weather Service.</instruction>
